    Semantics.Logger

    public class SemanticItem
extends Tracker.ShapeItem<MORPrimitive>
    A tracking Item based Tracker.ShapeItem and aMOR semantic mapping library.

    This object describes an Object by a semantics based on MORPrimitive, a shape based on (Tracker.ShapeItem) and an unique identifier based on OWLNamedIndividual.

    Moreover, it computes the probability of the object to being of a specific space and compute the probability to be update(MORPrimitive) to a new description (perceiving noise effects). Indeed, the probability is compute in term of scores by the updateScore(MORPrimitive) (see computeScore(double, double, long)) and than normaliseScores() (see also normaliseCounters()). This computation is base on counting own many times this object as be considered of a determinate shape and which is the probability that a perception was failing with respect to new scans (see: Tracker.SemanticObjectItem constants).

      • update

        public Tracker.UpdatingState update(MORPrimitive object)

        This method checks:

        • if this.equals( object) and return an Semantics.MappingState.ERROR if this is not true.
        • updates this belied (getShapeCnt() and isUpdated())
        • than, check if updateScore(MORPrimitive) is true.
        • if yes
          • replace ths semantic object with the input parameter.
          • return a Semantics.WritingState.UPDATED outcome.
        • if Tracker.ShapeItem.shapeAs(Semantics.Primitive) is true
          • makes an Semantics.Primitive#average(Semantics.Primitive) between ths semantic object with the input parameter.
          • return a Tracker.UpdatingState.AVERAGED outcome.
        • if false, return a Semantics.MappingState.NOT_CHANGED outcome.
        • it normaliseScores() always before to return.
        Parameters:
        object - the new belief describing a semantic object about this tracking Item.
        Returns:
        the updating state changes of the tacked item of updating it with the input belief.

      • updateScore

        protected boolean updateScore(MORPrimitive object)

        For each shapes S, defined by SemanticItem it:

        • update the relate score to be in the current belief through:
          SScore = computeScore(double, double, long)( SScore, S2S_PROBABILITY, ++SCnt);
        • than it check for all possible shapes of input objects E:
          • update the relate score to be in to check if it is bettwe to move to the new belief through:
            EScore = computeScore(double, double, long)( EScore, S2E_PROBABILITY, ++ECnt);
          • return EScore >? SScore
        Parameters:
        object - the new belief describing a semantic object about this tracking Item.
        Returns:
        true if the new belief seems to be more correct than the actual.

      • computeScore

        protected double computeScore(double score,
                              double transitionProbability,
                              long seenCount)
        Parameters:
        score - the actual score of this object to be of a new shape
        transitionProbability - the probability to corecclty change from this shape to the new belief.
        seenCount - how many time this Object has been classified with the new belief previously (see: normaliseCounters)
        Returns:
        return score + transitionProbability * seenCount;.
        This value should be overwritten to the given score.

      • normaliseScores

        protected void normaliseScores()
        Normalise all the scores between [0,1] by using: x_norm = (x - min) / (max - min).

      • normaliseCounters

        protected void normaliseCounters()
        Normalise all the scores between [0,MAX_NORMALISATION_COUNTER] by using: x_norm = (x - min) / (max - min). This is trigger when a counter reaches the RESET_COUNTER_VALUE, it is used only for avoiding stack overflow errors due to the continuously increasing of the counters.

      • finaliseUpdates

        public void finaliseUpdates()
        This method should be called from a tracking set interface (see: Tracker) in order to store if this item has not been updated in the last scan. It effects getShapeCnt() by decreasing the counter and triggers normaliseCounters() is a counter is grather than or equal RESET_COUNTER_VALUE

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        This methods assure that objects are collected in a set by id. It returns true if:
        • the two Items have the same unique identifier.
        • this Item have an ID equal to the simulateId(MORPrimitive) of the given object.
        • this Item have an ID equal to the given value.

        REMARK: the equality is not symmetric.
        Overrides:

        Tracker.Item.equals(Object)
